gde2-panel
===========

gde2-panel contains the GDE2 panel, the libgde2-panel-applet library and
several applets:

  + the GDE2 panel is the area on your desktop from which you can run
    applications and applets, and perform other tasks.

  + the libgde2-panel-applet library allows to develop small applications
    which may be embedded in the panel. These are called applets.
    Documentation for the API is available with gtk-doc.

  + the applets supplied here include the Workspace Switcher, the Window
    List, the Window Selector, the Notification Area, the Clock and the
    infamous 'Wanda the Fish'.

You may download updates to the package from:

   http://pub.gde2-desktop.org/releases/

gde2-panel is a fork of gnome-panel.

Installation
============

See the file 'INSTALL'. If you are not using a released version of
gde2-panel (for example, if you checked out the code from git), you
first need to run './autogen.sh'.


How to report bugs
==================

Bugs should be reported to the GDE2 bug tracking system:

   https://github.com/gde2-desktop/gde2-panel/issues

You will need to create an account for yourself.

Please read the HACKING file for information on where to send changes or
bugfixes for this package.
